ympics in her native Japan.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6247332659252145, \"rank\": 0.6006831307734164, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1305, \"end\": 1310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4314539664000013e-11, \"text\": \"Osaka\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\"}, {\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\", \"score\": 0.9999991808857602, \"rank\": 8.18475081668757e-07, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Born in the city that holds the same name as the world-ranked 102 tennis player, Osaka lit the Olympic cauldron for the games in Japan.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1500, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4314539664000013e-11, \"text\": \"Osaka\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\"}, {\"begin\": 1548, \"end\": 1553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\", \"score\": 0.9999991808857602, \"rank\": 8.18475081668757e-07, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then seeded second - while also ranked number two in the world - Osaka was defeated by Czechia's Marketa Vondrousova, who would go on to lose the final to Belinda Bencic of Switzerland.\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1740, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1620, \"end\": 1625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4314539664000013e-11, \"text\": \"Osaka\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\"}, {\"begin\": 1642, \"end\": 1649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"score\": 0.963280577361741, \"rank\": 0.025313850008774202, \"text\": \"Czechia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czech_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark\\u00e9ta_Vondrou\\u0161ov\\u00e1\", \"score\": 0.9999999999140528, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marketa Vondrousova\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark\\u00e9ta_Vondrou\\u0161ov\\u00e1\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark\\u00e9ta_Vondrou\\u0161ov\\u00e1\"}, {\"begin\": 1710, \"end\": 1724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belinda_Bencic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Belinda Bencic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belinda_Bencic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belinda_Bencic\"}, {\"begin\": 1728, \"end\": 1739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999343792072984, \"rank\": 6.53945075031731e-05, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The right-hander has four Grand Slam titles to her name, the US Open in 2018 and 2020 and Australian Open in 2019 and 2021, and is on the comeback trail after taking a lengthy break from the game for the birth of her first child.\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1774, \"end\": 1778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\", \"score\": 0.9999999999822649, \"rank\": 1.7901221669875703e-11, \"text\": \"Slam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Osaka returned to action as a wild card at the Australian Open this year but has failed to make it beyond the second round in the three Grand Slams to date in 2024.\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 2137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4314539664000013e-11, \"text\": \"Osaka\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\", \"Q13219666\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2009_HP_Open\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is hoping to turn her season around with a medal at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2138, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fresh from his Wimbledon final defeat by Alcaraz, Djokovic will be eager for an immediate return to his winning ways at Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2256, \"end\": 2263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8941750102292745e-17, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 2265, \"end\": 2273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.048377408171211e-18, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 2335, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.328196591147661e-12, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-old holds the record for the most weeks ranked number one in world tennis and currently sits second behind Italy's Jannik Sinner.\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2467, \"end\": 2472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999694549982733, \"rank\": 3.054576294437314e-05, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2475, \"end\": 2488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jannik Sinner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a record 24 Grand Slam titles already to his name, the Olympics provide one last frontier for the Serbian to conquer.\", \"from\": 2491, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2594, \"end\": 2601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.99934301765895, \"rank\": 0.0006491810152087892, \"text\": \"Serbian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic's best Olympic performance to date is a bronze medal way back in 2008.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 2694, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2615, \"end\": 2623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.048377408171211e-18, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With three consecutive French Open titles to her name, world number one Swiatek is the heavy favourite in the women's singles at Roland-Garros in Paris.\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2842, \"end\": 2847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999458851, \"rank\": 5.3996837929969375e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Tokyo Olympics three years ago, the Pole was knocked out in the second round at her first games, just two months after winning her maiden French Open title.\", \"from\": 2850, \"to\": 3013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But given her love affair with the clay courts of Paris - she's won 31 of her last 32 matches at Roland-Garros - a golden summer is expected for Swiatek at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3015, \"to\": 3184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3065, \"end\": 3070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999458851, \"rank\": 5.3996837929969375e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an extraordinary move, Nadal withdrew from this year's Wimbledon Championships, citing his desire to focus on the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3212, \"end\": 3217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0679944176759503e-20, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-time Grand Slam champion is expected to play in both the singles and doubles tournaments in Paris.\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3413, \"end\": 3418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999458851, \"rank\": 5.3996837929969375e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadal has struck Olympic gold twice before, defeating Fernando Gonzalez at the Beijing Games and eight years later, partnering with Marc Lopez to win the 2016 doubles at Rio de Janeiro.\", \"from\": 3421, \"to\": 3606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3475, \"end\": 3492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fernando_Gonz\\u00e1lez\", \"score\": 0.8223349273016554, \"rank\": 0.2160493827160689, \"text\": \"Fernando Gonzalez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fernando_Gonz\\u00e1lez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fernando_Gonz\\u00e1lez\"}, {\"begin\": 3553, \"end\": 3563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marc_L\\u00f3pez\", \"score\": 0.9999999113779307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marc Lopez\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marc_L\\u00f3pez\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marc_L\\u00f3pez\"}, {\"begin\": 3591, \"end\": 3605, \"title\": \"ht